items.title: Tatiana Schlossberg, granddaughter of JFK and cousin of Health Secretary RFK Jr., dies of cancer at 35
items.description: Her death comes just weeks after she publicly revealed in The New Yorker that she had been diagnosed with acute myeloid leukemia.

items.title: Doctors Without Borders kicked out of Gaza: Israel suspends dozens of humanitarian organizations over new registration rules
items.description: Israel says the rules are aimed at preventing Hamas and other militant groups from infiltrating the aid organizations.

items.title: Buddhist monks peace-walking from Texas to DC persist even after being run over on highway outside Houston
items.description: One of the monks had “substantial leg injuries” and was flown by helicopter to a hospital in Houston, Dayton Interim Police Chief Shane Burleigh said.

items.title: An AI super-bull who just backed the Nvidia-Groq deal warns of a data center bust: ‘We foresee a significant financial crisis’
items.description: Alex Davis says third-party data-center developers will eventually be jilted by the hyperscalers they serve, and face a subsequent debt crisis.

items.title: No, the White House can’t defund the CFPB, judge says, just days before agency would run out of cash
items.description: At the heart of this case is whether budget bigwig Russell Vought can effectively shut down the agency and lay off all of the bureau's employees.
